cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image super-resolution using convolutional neural networks.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper deals with improving the spatial resolution of satellite images, which can be considered a form of graphics.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses a machine learning technique (CNN) to achieve its objective.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses a form of AI (CNN) to improve the resolution of satellite images.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper's approach could potentially be applied to improve the resolution of images captured by robots or drones.
